","Grades":{"SC_9Rb0HikouMWnL5Y":"0"},"index":0},{"ChoiceID":"2","Grades":{"SC_9Rb0HikouMWnL5Y":"1"},"index":1}],"Language":[],"NextAnswerId":1,"NextChoiceId":4,"QuestionDescription":"Claim 5 of 10 Linguists estimate that, while the average English speaker knows between 20,000 and...","QuestionText":"Claim 5 of 10<br>Linguists estimate that, while the average English speaker knows between 20,000 and 40,000 words, most people rely on a surprisingly small core set of just a few hundred words in day-to-day conversation. The richness of one's vocabulary, researchers suggest, often stays largely untapped in casual communication.","QuestionText_Unsafe":"Claim 5 of 10<br>A single day on Venus lasts longer than a full Venusian year. Venus rotates so slowly on its axis that completing one rotation takes more time than completing a full orbit around the Sun.","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function() {\n    var textContainer = this.getQuestionTextContainer();\n\n    \/\/ Get the original question text\n    var fullText = textContainer.innerText.trim();\n    var words = fullText.split(\/\\s+\/);\n\n    \/\/ Clear the text\n    textContainer.innerHTML = \"\";\n\n    \/\/ Total reveal time = 10 seconds\n    var totalRevealTime = 10000;\n    var wordSpeed = Math.max(50, Math.floor(totalRevealTime \/ words.length));\n\n    var i = 0;\n\n    function typeWord() {\n        if (i < words.length) {\n            textContainer.innerHTML += words[i] + \" \";\n            i++;\n            setTimeout(typeWord, wordSpeed);\n        }\n    }\n\n    typeWord();\n});","DataExportTag":"Science1","QuestionID":"QID241"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_3UyxHHFTl7Y7X5c","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID242","SecondaryAttribute":"How confident are you when you were making the choice?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"How confident are you when you were m