tion, takes about 243 Earth days. However, Venus completes its orbit around the Sun in just 225 Earth days. That means a day on Venus is technically longer than its entire year, a quirk in our unique Solar System.","QuestionText_Unsafe":"Claim 9 of 10<br>The planet Venus rotates so slowly on its axis that a single day, one full rotation, takes about 243 Earth days. However, Venus completes its orbit around the Sun in just 225 Earth days. That means a day on Venus is technically longer than its entire year, a quirk in our unique Solar System.","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"QuestionJS":false,"DataExportTag":"Q473","QuestionID":"QID473"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_3UyxHHFTl7Y7X5c","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID474","SecondaryAttribute":"Timing","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Timing","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Timing","Selector":"PageTimer","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","MinSeconds":15,"MaxSeconds":30},"QuestionDescription":"Timing","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"First Click"},"2":{"Display":"Last Click"},"3":{"Display":"Page Submit"},"4":{"Display":"Click Count"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":240,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Timing","DataExportTag":"Q474","QuestionID":"QID474"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_3UyxHHFTl7Y7X5c","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID475","SecondaryAttribute":"Please wait, the system is processing...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please wait, the system is processing...","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please wait, the system is processing...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerI